    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-05-30T15:55:02+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-30T15:55:02+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-30T06:25:02Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-30T06:25:02Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A cold front about the southeast moves into Victoria overnight. A weak high pressure system moves across from the west on Sunday. A significant low pressure system moves over waters to the south of SA on Monday and Tuesday reaching western Bass Strait Tuesday afternoon. A another low pressure moves over waters to the southeast on Wednesday. A high pressure system follows the low moving across northern parts of SA later in the week.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW015" description="Mount Lofty Ranges" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-05-30T15:10:23+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-31T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-30T05:40:23Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-30T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. High chance of showers, becoming less likely in the evening. Winds westerly 20 to 30 km/h.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-05-31T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-01T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-30T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-31T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Medium chance of showers, most likely at night. Winds westerly 15 to 25 km/h becoming light in the early afternoon then becoming northerly 15 to 20 km/h in the late evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 7 and 11 with daytime temperatures reaching between 13 and 17.</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection not recommended, UV Index predicted to reach 2 [Low]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-06-01T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-02T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-31T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-01T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Very high chance of showers. The chance of a thunderstorm in the afternoon and evening, possibly severe with heavy rain which may lead to flash flooding about the southern Fleurieu Peninsula in the afternoon. Damaging winds possible. Winds northerly 15 to 25 km/h increasing to 25 to 40 km/h in the early morning then turning northwesterly 30 to 45 km/h in the early afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to around 9 with daytime temperatures reaching between 17 and 21.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-06-02T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-03T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-01T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-02T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Very high chance of showers. The chance of a thunderstorm in the morning. Damaging winds possible. Winds northwesterly 30 to 45 km/h turning westerly 30 to 40 km/h during the morning. Overnight temperatures falling to around 12 with daytime temperatures reaching between 14 and 18.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="4" start-time-local="2026-06-03T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-04T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-02T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-03T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Very high chance of showers. Winds westerly 25 to 35 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to around 10 with daytime temperatures reaching between 13 and 17.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
